16/09/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Greek Ombudsman Jorgos Kaminis visited Tirana on Thursday (15 September) at the invitation of Albanian counterpart Ermir Dobjani.
They discussed ways to enhance co-operation between their two institutions, as well as problems such as the rights and status of Albanian immigrants in Greece.
Kaminis also met with Parliament Speaker Jozefina Topalli.
In other news, Albania is hosting an international NATO military exercise this week in Vlora Bay.
The drills include co-ordination of land, air and sea operations, especially with regard to possible terrorism threats.
(Albanian News - 16/09/05)
